solutions.Solution 2 (Area Subtraction):
Clearly, $ABED$ is a square with side-length $3.$
Let the brackets denote areas. We apply area subtraction to find the area of $\triangle BEC:$
\begin{align*} [BEC]&=[ABCD]-[ABED] \\ &=\frac{AB+CD}{2}\cdot AD - AB^2 \\ &=\frac{3+6}{2}\cdot 3 - 3^2 \\ &=\boxed{\textbf{(B)}\ 4.5}. \end{align*}
